"n.推动力；刺激 【英】 n. 推动力; 刺激(incentive; impulse) 【记】 im(进入)+pet (追求)+us→内心追求 →推动力 【同】 同根词：competition (竞争，角逐) n. 推动力; 刺激 = incentive = impulse; 刺激物 = stimulus 【记】im进入, pet追求, us我们－进入追求我们的状态, 因为受了刺激, 因为看到我们都去了哈佛－推动力 【参】competitor(n 竞争者) 【记】im + pete 寻求, compete 竞争；im 不 + pet 宠物；不像宠物那样乖，温柔，而是猛烈，暴力 impetus (n.)  early 15c., impetous ""rapid movement, rush;"" 1640s, with modern spelling, ""force with which a body moves, driving force,"" from Latin impetus ""attack, assault, onset, impulse, violence, vigor, force, passion,"" related to impetere ""to attack,"" from assimilated form of in- ""into, in, on, upon"" (see in- (2)) + petere ""aim for, rush at"" (see petition (n.))."
